git status = to check the status of the repository
git init = create a new repository
git add = to add to the staging area
echo = to input txt or words in a file
git commit = to commit changes
git reseet = to reversed the state of a file or dir
git log = to see commit history
git log --oneline = to see commit history in a summarize format
git branch = to create a new branch
git merge = to merge two branches
git push = to push a repository to a git tool like github
git fetch = to fetch a directory without merging to local repository
git pull = to fetch and merge a directory with local repository
